THE memorial service for musician, Mthandeni Mvelase, is underway at the Market Theatre. Mthandeni, who created music for TV and theatre productions such as Township Fever and Muvhango, as well as Gibson Kente’s How Long, died on Thursday, 21 July. Mvelase had worked with singers such as the late Jabu Khanyile, Khululiwe Sithole, Lindelani Mkhize, Sipho Sithole, Faca Kulu, Shabalala Rhythms, Themba Mkhize, and Sibongile Khumalo. ALSO READ: Soccer star Andile smitten by bae! His cause of death is still unknown. According to his sister, Khululiwe Khanyile: “I was the first family member who was called. I was told he was taken to a hospital in Durban by an Uber and the message given to the driver was that he had a heart attack. “However, at the hospital they found it was a natural death. They took him to the mortuary for a post mortem to see what killed him.”